abstract: Hillary Clinton wins double-digit victories in Florida, North Carolina and Ohio Democratic primaries, rebounding from upset by Sen Bernie Sanders in Michigan and dealing major blow to his hopes of nomination; voters appear to respond to Clinton's arguments about trade and economy, talking points important to Sanders's campaign as well.
lead_paragraph: Hillary Clinton won a major victory in Ohio after an upset loss to Bernie Sanders in Michigan last week. She also won in Illinois, Florida and North Carolina.

byline.original: By PATRICK HEALY and AMY CHOZICK
byline.contributor: Trip Gabriel and Dalia Sussman contributed reporting.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Wins 4 Races, Rebounding From Michigan Loss
headline.print_headline: Voters Reject Sanders in Ohio as Clinton Rebounds From Michigan
